# Review and Quality

Use when reviewing code (self-review or PR). Ref: [Cursor Rules](https://cursor.com/docs/context/rules), [intent-driven SDD](https://intent-driven.dev/knowledge/best-practices/).

## Code review rubric

Score each dimension; block merge on "No" for correctness or security.

| Dimension | Questions | Pass criteria |
|-----------|-----------|----------------|
| **Correctness** | Does it match the spec/task? Edge cases and errors handled? | Behavior matches acceptance criteria; no obvious bugs. |
| **Tests** | New paths covered? Existing tests still pass? | New logic has tests; no regressions. |
| **DX** | Readable, navigable, consistent with the repo? | Naming/structure align with `@coding-standards.mdc`. |
| **Architecture** | SOLID respected? New smells introduced? Dependencies flow inward? | No new bloaters, couplers, or change preventers (see `@architecture-and-design.mdc`). |
| **Perf** | N+1 queries? Unbounded loops? Huge payloads? | No clear performance regressions for the change scope. |
| **Security** | Inputs validated? Secrets out of code/logs? Safe file/network access? | No new security issues; secrets not exposed. |

- **Correctness**: If the task has acceptance criteria, each must be demonstrably met.
- **Tests**: Prefer automated tests for business logic and APIs. Document intentional gaps.
- **Architecture**: Check for long methods, primitive obsession, feature envy, shotgun surgery, speculative generality. If a smell is found, the fix can be a follow-up task but must be tracked.
- **Security**: No hardcoded secrets; no logging of credentials or PII; sanitize inputs at boundaries.

## Pre-commit (suggested)

Run before every commit:

1. Lint: project linter (e.g. ESLint, Ruff).
2. Format: formatter (e.g. Prettier, Black).
3. Tests: full suite or scope to changed files if supported.
4. Typecheck: if the stack has one (e.g. `tsc --noEmit`).

Suggested tooling (do not install unless asked): pre-commit hooks (e.g. [husky](https://github.com/typicode/husky) + lint-staged), or `./scripts/verify.sh`. Ref: [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/).

## CI (suggested)

- Do not assume a specific CI provider; adapt to GitHub Actions, GitLab CI, Jenkins, etc.
- Pipeline: checkout > install deps > lint > test > typecheck > build. Optional: security scan (dependency audit) on main/release.
- Branch policy: passing CI before merge; optional approval for non-trivial changes.

## When NOT to apply

- Quick formatting-only or comment-only changes: minimal review; still run verify.
- Emergency hotfixes: correctness and security are mandatory; other dimensions deferred as follow-up.
